data.name: pev_string_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of string variables.

data.name: pev_classname
data.Description: Type of entity (Value of this controls what code handles the entity's think at pev_nextthink)

data.name: pev_globalname
data.Description: This is the name of the global variable (set by an env_global entity) that can be used to control the state of the entity.

data.name: pev_model
data.Description: The model of the entity

data.name: pev_target
data.Description: Entity that this entity is handling

data.name: pev_targetname
data.Description: The name given to this entity that another entity searches for to handle it

data.name: pev_netname
data.Description: Player or NPC name

data.name: pev_noise
data.Description: Noise variables do different things for different ents.

data.name: pev_noise1
data.Description: This is the move sound for doors.

data.name: pev_noise2
data.Description: This is the stop sound for doors.

data.name: pev_noise3
data.Description: This is for blocking game_player_equip and player_weaponstrip

data.name: pev_string_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_edict_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of edict variables.

data.name: pev_dmg_inflictor
data.Description: The entity that dealt damage to this entity. (If a gun deals the damage the gun's pev_owner is the entity who dealt the damage).

data.name: pev_aiment
data.Description:
Contains the entity's index that this entity is following. This is only in effect if this ent's movetype is MOVETYPE_FOLLOW.
Example:
set_pev(ent,pev_movetype,MOVETYPE_FOLLOW);
set_pev(ent,pev_aiment,index);

data.name: pev_owner
data.Description: Parent of this entity. For weapons this entity is the player.

data.name: pev_groundentity
data.Description: The index of the entity we're standing on.

data.name: pev_edict_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_float_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of float variables.

data.name: pev_nextthink
data.Description: The time (in relevance to get_gametime()) of the next time this entity's think will be called.

data.name: pev_gravity
data.Description:
0.0 = No gravity
1.0 = Normal Gravity
Values are not limited to 0.0 through 1.0

data.name: pev_friction
data.Description:
0.0 = No Friction (0 Acceleration)
1.0 = Normal Friction
>1.0 = Faster Acceleration + Faster Halt
negative value = Constant Acceleration in backwards direction

data.name: pev_frame
data.Description: The frame of the current sequence of the current model (Starts at frame 0.0)

data.name: pev_animtime
data.Description: The time to start the animation of the sequence (if sequence is running this is set to get_gametime())

data.name: pev_framerate
data.Description: The frames per second (FPS) the current sequence is playing at

data.name: pev_scale
data.Description: Doesn't affect models. Used for such things as env_sprites (stores sprite scale) or env_shooter (stores gib size)

data.name: pev_renderamt
data.Description:
The intensity of the render effects (0 = no effect 255 = full effect).
Don't think the value of this matters when the render mode is kRenderNormal (0)

data.name: pev_health
data.Description: Health of the entity. When it reaches 0 it is destroyed.

data.name: pev_frags
data.Description:
# of frags
Scoreboard changes when the ScoreInfo message is called.

data.name: pev_takedamage
data.Description:
Damage multiplyer
0.0 = Invincible
2.0 = Normal Damage

data.name: pev_max_health
data.Description: Always set to 100 but doesn't effect entities. I think it is just for reference. Players always respawn at 100.0 but I don't know if non-player entities spawn with this much HP when DLL_Func_Spawn is called. will have to test.

data.name: pev_teleport_time
data.Description: ? - Counts back from 2000.0 whenever I get out of the water (when the game moves your player upwards to represent climbing out).

data.name: pev_armortype
data.Description: Type of armor the entity has (In CS this is the CsArmorType constants).

data.name: pev_armorvalue
data.Description: Amount of armor the entity has.

data.name: pev_dmg_take
data.Description: Amount of damage entity was hit for.

data.name: pev_dmg
data.Description: Damage type that this entity got hit by (DMG_ constants).

data.name: pev_dmgtime
data.Description: On grenades, the time (in relevance to get_gametime()) at which the explosion should take place.

data.name: pev_speed
data.Description: Not for players. Effects change from entity to entity (IE: used for door swing speed)

data.name: pev_air_finished
data.Description:
Default: get_gametime() + 12.0
Number is set according to the previous equation every think unless a player is submerged under water.
if(get_gametime()==pev_air_finished + x)
{Deal Damage}
where x is any positive integer including 0.

data.name: pev_pain_finished
data.Description: ? - Guess would be that this is set to a gametime when you are set on fire or something of the sort.

data.name: pev_radsuit_finished
data.Description: ? - Guess would be that this is set to a gametime for how long the radiation suit lasts for maps like rock in TFC.

data.name: pev_maxspeed
data.Description: Think uses this to determine the max speed a player or monster can move at when fully accelerated.

data.name: pev_fov
data.Description:
Field of View
Determines how many degrees of view fit on the screen.
Default for players: 90.0
Smaller numbers are used for scoping.

data.name: pev_flFallVelocity
data.Description:
velocity[2] *= -1.0
Opposite of Z velocity (Falling Speed)

data.name: pev_fuser2
data.Description: [In CS]: When jump button is pressed this variable is set to 1320.0 and decreaments to 0.0. With default friction when this variable reads 0.0 the player should have the ability to accelerate like normal after landing from a jump. This variable does not affect this occurrence but monitors it.

data.name: pev_float_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_int_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of integer variables.

data.name: pev_fixangle
data.Description: When set to 1 it forces the client to update its angles to the ones set in pev_viewangles during the next player think

data.name: pev_modelindex
data.Description: Model index returned by precache_model.

data.name: pev_viewmodel
data.Description: Use pev_viewmodel2

data.name: pev_weaponmodel
data.Description: Use pev_weaponmodel2

data.name: pev_movetype
data.Description: Movement Type Constant. Further detail later

data.name: pev_solid
data.Description:
Solid Type Constant.
SOLID_NOT = No clipping, No touching, No hitboxes
SOLID_TRIGGER = No clipping, Touching, No hitboxes
SOLID_BBOX = Clipping, Touching, Hitboxes
SOLID_SLIDEBOX = Clipping, Touching, Hitboxes, Friction when moving, Players and monsters use this
SOLID_BSP = No Clipping, Touching, Hitboxes

data.name: pev_skin
data.Description: Selects the skin the model displays. Most models only have 1 skin (skin 0).

data.name: pev_body
data.Description:
Part of a model.
pev_body = 1 shows backpack in CS

data.name: pev_effects
data.Description: Bitsum of preset draw effects for an entity (EF_ constants in hlsdk_const.inc)

data.name: pev_light_level
data.Description: Amount of light shining on the entity (Used for model rendering) (0=No light 180=Fully Lit).

data.name: pev_sequence
data.Description:
Primary sequence the entity runs
If player or monster this is the sequence of the lower body parts (IE: run / sequence 4 in CS)

data.name: pev_gaitsequence
data.Description: Secondary sequence for monsters and players that shows upper body animation (IE: ref_aim_mp5 / sequence 36 in CS)

data.name: pev_rendermode
data.Description: The type of rendering for the model / how the model is rendered.

data.name: pev_renderfx
data.Description: The effects added to the model rendering.

data.name: pev_weapons
data.Description: Bitsum of all currently carried weapons for a player.

data.name: pev_deadflag
data.Description:
Flags dealing with player's death status
0 - alive
1 - playing death animation or still falling off of a ledge waiting to hit ground
2 - dead, lying still.
3 - ?
4 - ?

data.name: pev_button
data.Description:
Bit flag for what buttons are currently being held by the player
IN_ constants

data.name: pev_impulse
data.Description:
When set it activates impulse commands during think (Resets to 0.0 after impulse occurs) (Impulses can be found in player.cpp).
Non-Mod specific impulses:
99 - Valve/Sierra Logo
100 - Flashlight
201 - Logo Spray

data.name: pev_spawnflags
data.Description: Bit flag of entity's spawn flags (SF_ constants (hlsdk_const.inc)).

data.name: pev_flags
data.Description: bit flag of entity flags (FL_ constants)

data.name: pev_team
data.Description: Team of the entity (Use mod specific team constants). I think it can only be extracted as an int which may be why it is displaying 0.0 on my reading even though I was on the T team.

data.name: pev_waterlevel
data.Description:
0 - Not in water
1 - Waiding
2 - Mostly submerged
3 - Completely submerged

data.name: pev_watertype
data.Description:
-1 - No water
-3 - Water
-4 - Slim
-5 - Lava

data.name: pev_playerclass
data.Description:
Not used in CS.
Class constant in other games (IE: DODC_GARAND / TFC_PC_SCOUT)

data.name: pev_weaponanim
data.Description: Sequence of the v_ model.

data.name: pev_bInDuck
data.Description:
0 - Not in the process of ducking
1 - In the process of ducking
Note: if fully crouched this returns 0

data.name: pev_flTimeStepSound
data.Description: ? - Starts at 400.0 and decreases to 0.0 then resets to 400.0 and repeats constantly.

data.name: pev_flDuckTime
data.Description: When crouch button is pressed this variable is set to 1000.0 and decreaments to 0.0. If crouch button is released variable is instantly reset to 0.0.

data.name: pev_iStepLeft
data.Description: Seems to control which footstep sound is played. Toggles between 1.0 and 0.0 every time a footstep sound occurs for the player.

data.name: pev_gamestate
data.Description:
Don't know exactly what this does but in CS:
1.0 = No Shield
0.0 = Shield

data.name: pev_oldbuttons
data.Description:
Bit flag of the buttons that the player was pressing during the last think
IN_ constants

data.name: pev_int_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_byte_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of byte variables.

data.name: pev_byte_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_bytearray_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of byte array variables.

data.name: pev_bytearray_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.name: pev_vecarray_start
data.Description: Placeholder. Start of vector(Float:[3]) array variables.

data.name: pev_origin
data.Description: [3] Location of the entity in the map

data.name: pev_oldorigin
data.Description: [3] Doesn't seem to be used anymore

data.name: pev_velocity
data.Description: [3] Vector speed of entity

data.name: pev_basevelocity
data.Description: [3] Velocity of the conveyor we are standing.

data.name: pev_movedir
data.Description: [3] For waterjumping, a forced forward velocity so we can fly over lip of ledge.

data.name: pev_angles
data.Description:
[3] Angles for model rendering.
[0] = Verticle (90=Looking down | -90=Looking up)
[1] = Horizontal (-180/180 = Looking backward | 90 = Looking Left | -90 = Looking Right | 0 = Looking Straight)

data.name: pev_avelocity
data.Description: [3] Rotating Velocity (More Research Coming)

data.name: pev_v_angle
data.Description: [3] Angles for player view rendering. Same numbers as angles.

data.name: pev_absmin
data.Description:
[3] These 2 variables are used by the engine for calculations and are set automatically for all entities
pev_origin[i] + pev_mins[i] - 1

data.name: pev_absmax
data.Description: [3] pev_origin[i] + pev_maxs[i] + 1

data.name: pev_mins
data.Description: [3] Negative distance away from the origin on each axis the entity is touchable / clippable

data.name: pev_maxs
data.Description: [3] Positive distance away from the origin on each axis the entity is touchable / clippable

data.name: pev_size
data.Description: [3] pev_size[i] = abs(pev_mins[i] - pev_maxs[i])

data.name: pev_rendercolor
data.Description:
[3] = {R, G, B}
Color to use with pev_rendermode

data.name: pev_view_ofs
data.Description: [3] Permanent version of pev_punchangle

data.name: pev_punchangle
data.Description: [2] Offset of v_angles usually due to recoil or being shot. pev_punchangles decreases to 0.0 gradually/automatically

data.name: pev_vecarray_end
data.Description: Placeholder.

data.Description: The weapon model other players see as the weapon being carried by the player (p_ models)

data.name: pev_viewmodel2
data.Description: The weapon model displayed to the character in first person (v_ models)
